"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_N_E=self.webpackChunk_N_E||[]).push([[557],{6557:function(e,t,o){o.r(t),o.d(t,{LOVESICK:function(){return a}});let a={id:"lovesick",title:"The Lovesick Pirate",shortDescription:"Hopelessly smitten with a beautiful merfolk creature.",skillGrid:{exploration:["star","open","open","star","star","blocked","blocked"],brawn:["star","open","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked"],hunting:["star","open","star","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked"],aim:["star","star","open","open","blocked","blocked","blocked"],swagger:["star","open","open","star","star","star","blocked"],navigation:["star","star","open","star","blocked","blocked","blocked"]},constellation:o(9774).g0,storyBlanks:[{number:1,prompt:"A name for your merfolk love interest",type:"text"},{number:2,prompt:"A romantic pet name",type:"text"},{number:3,prompt:"Something you find attractive",type:"text"},{number:4,prompt:"The pirate name of another player",type:"player_name"},{number:5,prompt:"A love poem, four words or less",type:"text"}],backstory:"I've been in love exactly once in my life, and it ruined me. It was three years ago, on a moonlit night, when I saw them rise from the waves. {1}, the most beautiful merfolk creature I had ever seen. Their {3} glistened in the moonlight, and when they looked at me with those deep ocean eyes, I knew I was done for.\n\nWe had one perfect night. Just me and my {2}, sittin' on the rocks, talkin' about the tides and the stars. When dawn came, {1} disappeared beneath the waves, and I've been searchin' for them ever since. The other pirates think I'm daft. {4} says I probably just saw a particularly attractive dolphin. But I know what I saw, and I know what I felt.\n\nI've composed {5} in their honor, which I sing every night at the bow of the ship, much to the annoyance of literally everyone aboard. I don't care. Love makes you do foolish things, and I've fully embraced the foolishness. Every wave, every splash, every ripple — I look for {1}. I will find my {2} again, even if I have to sail to the edge of the world.",events:[{narrative:"I thought I saw {1} in the water today! It turned out to be a manatee, but for one glorious moment, my heart sang. {4} patted me on the shoulder and said, \"Maybe next time.\" They're surprisingly supportive for someone who thinks I'm insane.",effect:"Re-roll +1. Discontent -1."},{narrative:"A message in a shell washed up on deck. Inside was a tiny pearl and a note that read: \"I hear your song every night. Do not stop singing. — {1}.\" MY LOVE HEARD ME! {4} thinks I wrote it myself, but I know {1}'s handwriting! Well, I don't actually, but I FEEL it.",effect:"Treasure +1. Re-roll +2."},{narrative:"We sailed through waters that glowed with bioluminescence, and among the lights, I saw figures dancing beneath the waves. Merfolk! And among them — was that {1}? I leapt to the rail, and for a moment, I swear one of them waved at me. I waved back so enthusiastically I nearly fell overboard. {4} grabbed my belt just in time.",effect:"Retrieve card 71 Siren's Locket from the story deck."},{narrative:"I've been learning to hold my breath for longer and longer periods, in case I need to swim down to {1}'s kingdom. My record is now quite impressive, though {4} says the amount of time I spend with my face in a bucket of water is \"deeply concerning.\"",effect:"Gain 1 skill of your choice. Swagger +1."},{narrative:'THEY CAME BACK! Just for a moment, in the middle of the night, {1} surfaced next to the ship and touched my hand! Their {3} was even more beautiful than I remembered! "{2}," I whispered. They smiled, said "Soon," and disappeared. I haven\'t slept since. I may never sleep again. WHO NEEDS SLEEP WHEN YOU HAVE LOVE?!',effect:"Re-roll +3. Infamy +1."}],endings:{bad:{threshold:"≤3",text:"You never find {1} again. You spend years sailing every ocean, singing {5} to the waves every night, but the merfolk never return. {4} eventually can't take the constant singing anymore and transfers to another ship. Alone and heartbroken, you retire to a seaside cottage where you carve wooden merfolk figurines and sell them to tourists. They're actually quite good. You become locally famous as \"that weird pirate who fell in love with a fish.\" Every night you sit on the rocks where you first met {1}, holding the pearl from their message, and you sing your song to the sea. The sea, at least, always listens."},good:{threshold:"4",text:"After years of searching, {1} finds YOU. They surface one calm evening and take you by the hand. \"I've been watching you search for me,\" they say. \"Your devotion has moved the mer-court. They've agreed to let you visit our kingdom.\" Using a magical pearl, you're able to breathe underwater for short periods. You split your time between the surface and {1}'s underwater world. It's not a conventional relationship — {4} calls it \"logistically challenging\" — but when you're sitting on a coral throne, holding hands with the most beautiful creature you've ever seen, convention doesn't seem to matter. You write a book of love poetry that becomes a bestseller. All the poems are just {5} in different arrangements."},legendary:{threshold:"5",text:"{1} returns in the company of the entire mer-court, hundreds of merfolk surfacing in the moonlight. They've come to offer you a choice: drink from the Cup of Tides and become merfolk yourself, living forever with {1} in the deep kingdom, or remain human and receive the mer-court's blessing and protection for the rest of your days. You choose to drink, and as the transformation takes hold, you feel your {3} changing, gills opening, and a tail replacing your legs. {1} catches you as you slip into the water. \"Welcome home, {2},\" they say. {4} watches from the ship's rail as you disappear beneath the waves, hand in hand with your love. A single tear rolls down their cheek. They'll miss you, but they know you're finally where you belong. Your song, {5}, becomes a folk melody sung by sailors everywhere, a reminder that love can cross any boundary — even the one between land and sea."}}}}}]);